The kingdom protecting that village fought back the men, but the village was burned to ashes by the time anything could be done.  Sheyala and a few other children were the only survivors, but the others were but baby's and didn't survive.  The Queen herself took in Shey and raised her beside the princess as a guardian.  Sheyala grew up learning the arts of the sword and self defense. Finally as generations changed her princess married and became her Queen and things were peaceful for a time, but it didn't stay that way.<br>
Upon returning from a peace agreement, Shayala, Her Queen, and Her Queen found their castle under siege by centaurs, humans and others alike.  Lead by Tomais the head centaur, Dryisan a mage and Angelus and Vamp, the kingdom was destroyed.  Along With the now mythological creature the Phoenix that guarded it.  <br>
The King, The Queen, and Sheyala's Twins and husband were slain before her very eyes.  She again was the only survivor and as punisment  lives until the day that the souls of the lost are regained.  As, the three trapped them in a phoenix pendant that was broken into 4 pieces.  Sheyala stunned by all of this lie in the snow as she was left to fend for herself.  The dying phoenix the once so bravely protected it's kingdom gave its last powers to her, along with a satchel of its own fiery feathers.  These things gave SHeyala abilites beyond imaginable scale.<br>
Eventually Sheyala regans 2 pieces of the pendant, now owning three herself.  One more pice and she can die in piece and regain those that she sought to revenge. <br>
Soon after finiding the third piece of the pendant, Sheyala challenged the final guardian Angelus and was defeated.<br>
Lost and alone, she was found and taken in by the amazons of Themiscrya where she resides, training, and waiting for the day she can return home and kill the final enemy that stands in her way of eternal rest.<br>
